  "text": "## Grafana Datasource Plugin Query to Data Frame Chain\n\n### Complete Query Flow\n\nThe Grafana datasource plugin query flow from HTTP API handler to data frame response follows this chain:\n\n#### 1. HTTP Query Endpoint Handler (pkg/api/ds_query.go:QueryMetricsV2)\nThe entry point for datasource queries is the `QueryMetricsV2` function in `pkg/api/ds_query.go`. This function:\n- Receives HTTP POST requests to `/api/ds/query` endpoint\n- Deserializes the request body into `dtos.MetricRequest`\n- Delegates to `hs.queryDataService.QueryData()` or `hs.queryDataService.QueryDataNew()`\n- Returns the response through `response.JSONStreaming()` which handles data frame serialization\n\n#### 2. Query Service Orchestration (pkg/services/query/query.go)\nThe `ServiceImpl` type in `pkg/services/query/query.go` implements the core query orchestration:\n- `QueryData()` and `QueryDataNew()` are the public interface methods\n- `queryData()` is the internal implementation that:\n  - Parses metric request into queries grouped by datasource UID\n  - Handles expressions if present\n  - Routes to single datasource handler (`handleQuerySingleDatasource`) or multi-datasource handler (`executeConcurrentQueries`)\n  - Returns `backend.QueryDataResponse` containing the responses\n\n#### 3. Single Datasource Query Handler (pkg/services/query/query.go:handleQuerySingleDatasource)\nFor queries to a single datasource, this function:\n- Validates datasource access\n- Constructs `backend.QueryDataRequest` with all queries and plugin context\n- Calls `s.pluginClient.QueryData(ctx, req)` to execute the plugin\n- Returns the response which contains data frames from the plugin\n\n#### 4. Plugin Client Abstraction (pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/)\nThe plugin client layer bridges Grafana core with backend plugins:\n\n**ClientV2** (pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/client_v2.go):\n- The `QueryData()` method (line 162) receives `backend.QueryDataRequest`\n- Converts request to protobuf: `backend.ToProto().QueryDataRequest(req)`\n- Calls `c.DataClient.QueryData(ctx, protoReq)` through gRPC\n- Receives protobuf response and converts back: `backend.FromProto().QueryDataResponse(protoResp)`\n\n**ProtoClient** (pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/client_proto.go):\n- The `QueryData()` method (line 113) provides the gRPC client interface\n- Gets the `ClientV2` instance and delegates to `c.DataClient.QueryData(ctx, in, opts...)`\n- This makes the actual gRPC call to the plugin process\n\n#### 5. Plugin API Handler (pkg/aggregator/apiserver/plugin/query.go:QueryDataHandler)\nThis is the HTTP handler that the aggregator/plugin server implements:\n- Receives `QueryDataRequest` as JSON\n- Extracts datasource UID from URL path\n- Gets plugin context through `h.pluginContextProvider.GetPluginContext()`\n- Calls `h.client.QueryData()` to execute the actual plugin\n- Wraps response in `aggregationv0alpha1.QueryDataResponse`\n- Returns serialized response through HTTP\n\n#### 6. Data Frame Serialization\nData frames are returned in the `QueryDataResponse` which contains:\n- Map of RefID to `DataResponse` objects\n- Each `DataResponse` contains `Frames` (array of `*data.Frame`)\n- The `response.JSONStreaming()` function in the HTTP handler serializes these frames to JSON\n- Uses Apache Arrow format internally for efficient encoding of tabular data\n\n### Key Files in the Query Chain\n\n1. **pkg/api/ds_query.go** - HTTP endpoint handler that receives /api/ds/query requests\n2. **pkg/services/query/query.go** - Core query service with routing logic for single/multi-datasource queries\n3. **pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/client_v2.go** - Backend plugin client that handles protobuf conversion and gRPC calls\n4. **pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/client_proto.go** - ProtoClient that provides low-level gRPC interface\n5. **pkg/aggregator/apiserver/plugin/query.go** - Plugin HTTP handler in aggregator/API server\n6. **pkg/api/response** - Response marshaling utilities that handle JSON streaming of data frames\n\n### Data Flow Summary\n\nHTTP POST /api/ds/query → QueryMetricsV2 → queryData → handleQuerySingleDatasource → pluginClient.QueryData (gRPC) → Plugin Backend → QueryDataResponse with Frames → toJsonStreamingResponse → JSON HTTP Response\n"
